---
import Docs from '../../layouts/Docs.astro'
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro'
import SeeAlso from '../../components/SeeAlso.astro'
import SpecLinks from '../../components/SpecLinks.astro'
import { Code } from 'astro-expressive-code/components'

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/+$/, '')
---

<Docs
  current="mapbox"
  title="X-GIS — Mapbox compatibility"
  description="Mapbox Style Spec coverage in the converter, the conceptual differences, and the migration path from Mapbox GL JS / MapLibre to xgis."
  headings={[
    { depth: 2, slug: 'mental-model', text: 'Mental model differences' },
    { depth: 2, slug: 'converter', text: 'Using the converter' },
    { depth: 2, slug: 'compatibility', text: 'Compatibility matrix' },
    { depth: 2, slug: 'expression-mapping', text: 'Expression mapping' },
    { depth: 2, slug: 'caveats', text: 'Caveats & gotchas' },
  ]}
>
  <header class="mb-12">
    <p class="text-[13px] font-medium text-accent mb-3 tracking-[-0.01em]">Guides</p>
    <h1 class="text-[36px] sm:text-[44px] lg:text-[52px] font-medium text-fg leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.035em]">
      Migrating from Mapbox.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-5 text-[16px] sm:text-[17px] leading-[1.6] text-fg-dim max-w-[720px]">
      X-GIS reads the Mapbox Style Spec — paste a <code class="font-mono text-fg">style.json</code>
      into <a href={`${base}/convert`} class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">/convert</a>
      and get an equivalent <code class="font-mono text-fg">.xgis</code> source. This page
      explains what carries across, what's heuristically lossy, and the
      conceptual differences between the two engines.
    </p>
  </header>

  <article class="space-y-14">

    <section>
      <h2 id="mental-model" class="scroll-mt-24 text-[24px] sm:text-[28px] font-medium text-fg leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-line">
        Mental model differences
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-fg-dim mb-6 max-w-[720px]">
        Mapbox GL JS is an imperative library — you instantiate
        a <code class="font-mono text-fg">Map</code>, call <code class="font-mono text-fg">addLayer()</code>,
        wire styling through paint property setters, ship glue code
        in JS. xgis is a language: the source <em>is</em> the program,
        and the compiler emits the WGSL.
      </p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-line bg-bg-elev p-5">
          <p class="text-[11px] font-medium text-fg-mute uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Mapbox</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-fg-dim">
            <li>• Imperative API — <code class="font-mono text-fg">map.addLayer({})</code></li>
            <li>• JSON style spec parsed at runtime</li>
            <li>• Expressions evaluated by a tree walker per frame</li>
            <li>• GLSL shaders hand-written for each paint property</li>
            <li>• Symbol layers (text, icons) first-class</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-line bg-bg-elev p-5">
          <p class="text-[11px] font-medium text-fg-mute uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">xgis</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-[13px] leading-[1.55] text-fg-dim">
            <li>• Declarative — <code class="font-mono text-fg">layer x &#123; … &#125;</code></li>
            <li>• Compile-time IR + WGSL codegen</li>
            <li>• Zoom-driven values lower to GPU uniforms</li>
            <li>• Per-feature expressions baked into vertex attributes</li>
            <li>• Symbol layers not yet implemented (text rendering pending)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <Callout type="note" title="What this means in practice">
        Most cartographic styles port cleanly. <strong>Text labels</strong>
        now render end-to-end via the SDF text pipeline — Mapbox
        <code class="font-mono">text-field</code>, <code class="font-mono">text-color</code>,
        <code class="font-mono">text-size</code>, <code class="font-mono">text-halo-*</code>,
        <code class="font-mono">text-anchor</code> and <code class="font-mono">text-transform</code>
        all map to <code class="font-mono">label-*</code> utilities and
        appear at the correct geographic anchor on every frame.
        Along-path road labels and collision detection arrive in the
        next batch; icons depend on the upcoming sprite atlas.
      </Callout>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="converter" class="scroll-mt-24 text-[24px] sm:text-[28px] font-medium text-fg leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-line">
        Using the converter
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-fg-dim mb-4 max-w-[720px]">
        Open <a href={`${base}/convert`} class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover underline">/convert</a>,
        click a preset chip (Liberty / Bright / Positron — three OpenFreeMap
        styles) or paste a URL pointing at any <code class="font-mono text-fg">style.json</code>.
        The page emits an <code class="font-mono text-fg">.xgis</code> source and
        a count badge showing how many features got dropped or rewritten.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-fg-dim mb-4 max-w-[720px]">
        The converter is also exported from the compiler package — call it
        from your build pipeline to bake conversions into your bundle.
      </p>
      <Code lang="js" code={`import { convertMapboxStyle } from '@xgis/compiler'

const style = await fetch('https://tiles.openfreemap.org/styles/bright')
  .then(r => r.json())
const xgis = convertMapboxStyle(style)
// xgis is a string — feed to <XGISMap>.run() directly.`} />
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="compatibility" class="scroll-mt-24 text-[24px] sm:text-[28px] font-medium text-fg leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-line">
        Compatibility matrix
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-[12.5px]">
        <div class="border border-line rounded-md p-4 bg-bg-elev">
          <div class="text-emerald-300 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2 font-medium">Supported</div>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-fg-dim leading-[1.55]">
            <li>• Sources: vector (PMTiles + TileJSON), raster, GeoJSON</li>
            <li>• Layers: background, fill, line, fill-extrusion, symbol (text)</li>
            <li>• Paint: fill-color/-opacity, line-color/-width/-dasharray/-opacity, fill-extrusion-color/-opacity/-height/-base</li>
            <li>• Symbol: text-field, text-color, text-size, text-halo-color/-width, text-anchor (5-way), text-transform</li>
            <li>• Filters: legacy + expression form (==/!=/&lt;/&gt;/all/any/in/!in/has/!has)</li>
            <li>• Expressions: get / coalesce / case / match / arithmetic / min / max / to-number</li>
            <li>• Zoom: <code class="font-mono">interpolate(zoom, …)</code> with linear curve</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-line rounded-md p-4 bg-bg-elev">
          <div class="text-amber-300 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2 font-medium">Lossy / heuristic</div>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-fg-dim leading-[1.55]">
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">interpolate</code> curve type (exponential / cubic-bezier) folded to linear</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">fill-translate</code>, <code class="font-mono">line-translate</code> dropped</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">fill-outline-color</code> emitted as a separate stroke layer when paired</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">$type</code> / <code class="font-mono">$id</code> filters dropped (geometry type implied by utility)</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">text-anchor</code> diagonals (top-left / etc.) collapse to dominant axis</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">text-size</code> expression form constant-only (zoom interpolate pending)</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">fill-pattern</code> / <code class="font-mono">line-pattern</code> dropped (bitmap atlases unimplemented)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="border border-line rounded-md p-4 bg-bg-elev">
          <div class="text-rose-300 text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wider mb-2 font-medium">Unsupported (engine)</div>
          <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-fg-dim leading-[1.55]">
            <li>• Icon symbols + sprite atlas (icon-image / icon-size / icon-color)</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">symbol-placement: line</code> (along-path road labels)</li>
            <li>• Text collision (text-allow-overlap, text-padding, text-ignore-placement)</li>
            <li>• Circle, heatmap, hillshade, sky layers</li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">let</code> / <code class="font-mono">var</code>, <code class="font-mono">downcase</code>, <code class="font-mono">number-format</code></li>
            <li>• <code class="font-mono">step</code> expressions, <code class="font-mono">at</code>, <code class="font-mono">distance</code></li>
            <li>• Top-level <code class="font-mono">light</code>, <code class="font-mono">fog</code>, <code class="font-mono">terrain</code></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="expression-mapping" class="scroll-mt-24 text-[24px] sm:text-[28px] font-medium text-fg leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-line">
        Expression mapping
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[14px] leading-[1.6] text-fg-dim mb-6 max-w-[720px]">
        Common Mapbox expressions and their xgis equivalents. The
        converter applies these automatically — this is for when you're
        reading converter output and want to know what changed.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div>
          <p class="text-[12px] font-medium text-fg-mute uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Zoom-driven width</p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <Code lang="json" title="Mapbox" code={`"line-width": [
  "interpolate", ["linear"],
  ["zoom"],
  11, 1,
  19, 2.5
]`} />
            <Code lang="xgis" title="xgis" code={`| stroke-[interpolate(zoom, 11, 1, 19, 2.5)]`} />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-[12px] font-medium text-fg-mute uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Property-driven color</p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <Code lang="json" title="Mapbox" code={`"fill-color": [
  "match",
  ["get", "class"],
  "park",  "#cfe7c1",
  "water", "#a4c8d5",
  "#dadada"
]`} />
            <Code lang="xgis" title="xgis" code={`| fill match(.class) {
    "park"  -> #cfe7c1
    "water" -> #a4c8d5
    _       -> #dadada
  }`} />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-[12px] font-medium text-fg-mute uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Coalesce fallback</p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <Code lang="json" title="Mapbox" code={`"fill-extrusion-height": [
  "coalesce",
  ["get", "render_height"],
  ["get", "height"],
  5
]`} />
            <Code lang="xgis" title="xgis" code={`| fill-extrusion-height-[.render_height ?? .height ?? 5]`} />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <p class="text-[12px] font-medium text-fg-mute uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Filter — legacy form</p>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <Code lang="json" title="Mapbox" code={`"filter": [
  "all",
  ["==", "$type", "LineString"],
  ["==", "class", "highway"]
]`} />
            <Code lang="xgis" title="xgis" code={`filter: .class == "highway"
// $type dropped — geometry type
// is implied by the utility used`} />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="caveats" class="scroll-mt-24 text-[24px] sm:text-[28px] font-medium text-fg leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.02em] mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-line">
        Caveats &amp; gotchas
      </h2>

      <Callout type="warning" title="Symbol layers are silently skipped">
        The converter emits a <code class="font-mono">// SKIPPED layer "…" type="symbol"</code>
        comment for every symbol layer it finds, and the conversion notes
        block at the bottom of the output lists them. You'll see a city
        with no labels until the runtime ships text rendering.
      </Callout>

      <Callout type="warning" title="TileJSON URLs need the right type">
        Mapbox sources without a <code class="font-mono">.pmtiles</code> extension
        are emitted as <code class="font-mono">type: tilejson</code> — the runtime
        fetches the manifest, then the per-tile <code class="font-mono">.pbf</code>.
        If the host doesn't send <code class="font-mono">Access-Control-Allow-Origin</code>,
        all tile fetches fail silently (the catalog stays empty).
      </Callout>

      <Callout type="tip" title="Curve type loses subtlety">
        Mapbox <code class="font-mono">["exponential", base]</code> curves get
        flattened to linear. For a smooth-feel close to the original add
        more stops in between — `interpolate(zoom, 11, 1, 14, 1.5, 18, 4)`
        approximates an exponential rise better than two endpoints alone.
      </Callout>

      <Callout type="note" title="Round-trip is not exact">
        The converter's goal is "produces a sensible visual approximation",
        not "byte-equivalent round-trip". For pixel-precise reproduction
        of an existing Mapbox map, plan some manual touch-up after
        running the converter.
      </Callout>
    </section>

  </article>

  <SpecLinks specs={[
    { body: 'Mapbox',  title: 'Mapbox Style Specification', url: 'https://docs.mapbox.com/style-spec/reference/' },
    { body: 'Mapbox',  title: 'Style spec — expressions', url: 'https://docs.mapbox.com/style-spec/reference/expressions/' },
    { body: 'MapLibre', title: 'MapLibre Style Spec (community fork)', url: 'https://maplibre.org/maplibre-style-spec/' },
  ]} />

  <SeeAlso links={[
    { label: 'Open the converter', href: `${base}/convert`, body: 'Try a public Mapbox style end-to-end.' },
    { label: 'Source types', href: `${base}/docs/sources`, body: 'How the converter routes Mapbox source URLs.' },
    { label: 'Expressions & operators', href: `${base}/docs/expressions`, body: 'Where the converted match() / interpolate() / ?? expressions land.' },
    { label: 'Function reference', href: `${base}/docs/functions`, body: 'The `interpolate(zoom, …)` / `step` / `match` builtin set.' },
  ]} />
</Docs>
